  "market_context": "Bullish rally wave followed by strong bearish momentum; price repeatedly swept identified buyside and sellside liquidity zones created at swing points.",
  "key_observation": "Price systematically swept multiple liquidity zones—buyside above swing highs and sellside below swing lows—with momentum candles, often reversing after the sweep.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the most recent swing high (with lower highs on both sides) and marked buyside liquidity just above it.",
    "Step 2: Identified a swing low (with higher lows on both sides) and marked sellside liquidity just below it.",
    "Step 3: Observed price sweeping the most recent sellside liquidity, then forming a new swing low (new sellside liquidity).",
    "Step 4: Noted price sweeping the buyside liquidity above the prior swing high, then forming a new swing high (new buyside liquidity).",
    "Step 5: Continued mapping additional swing points as they formed, observing repeated sweeps of newly generated liquidity zones with red momentum candles.",
    "Step 6: Highlighted that clustered buyside liquidity zones (e.g., two near each other) increase significance of the older zone."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Smart money targets liquidity at swing points to trigger stops; sequential sweeps indicate institutional accumulation/distribution. Traders should anticipate reversals after liquidity is taken out.",
